con-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550684040"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 800px !important; height: 244px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 400px 122px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 800px !important; height: 244px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-336495" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>Your shoulders are complex joints that are prone to injury.</p><p>Using a resistance band can help <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6383082/" class="" target="_blank">build strength</a> and stability while also helping to improve mobility in your shoulders with little risk of injury.</p><p>Resistance bands allow you to apply resistance at any angle without gravity. This will enable you to focus on specific areas in various angles of rotation.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1668706722700" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1668706722700"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>Can Be Modified for Personal Needs&nbsp;</strong></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665936192645" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1665936192645"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="widt